'''Awaji Shrine''' (あわちじんじゃ) is an {{ill|lt=Engishiki shrine|Q1342448|qid=Q1342448|lt=Engishiki|1=Engishiki}}. It is enshrined together at Nakatomi Itate Shrine in Ibo Town, Tatsuno City, Hyōgo Prefecture. During the Edo period, it was called Awaniwa Shrine.

It is believed to have been enshrined together in the main hall of Nakatomi Itate Shrine sometime from the medieval period through the mid-Edo period, but the “Jingishi-ryō” identifies it with Yobira Shrine.

=== Access ===
* JR {{ill|lt=Kishin Line|Q869221|qid=Q869221|1=Kishin Line}} {{ill|lt=Hon-Tatsuno Station|Q11520740|qid=Q11520740|1=Hon-Tatsuno Station}}, about 10 minutes by taxi
* JR {{ill|lt=San’yō Main Line|Q1193436|qid=Q1193436|1=San'yō Main Line}}{{ill|lt=Tatsuno Station|Q5366259|qid=Q5366259|1=Tatsuno Station (Hyōgo)}}, about 10 minutes by taxi
* About 5 minutes north from the “Nishikama Intersection,” the terminus of {{ill|lt=National Route 2|Q1131340|qid=Q1131340|1=Japan National Route 2}}{{ill|lt=Taishi–Tatsuno Bypass|Q11443881|qid=Q11443881|1=Prince Tatsuno bypass}}

